---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  lang="en"
  title="About | Tsatsin"
  description="What this site is, what content lives here, and how posts are published."
>
  <section class="hero about-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">About this site</p>
    <h1>A field log from Telegram, published as a searchable archive.</h1>
    <p class="about-lede">
      This is where raw notes become public threads: model behavior, product edge-cases,
      hardware detours, and occasional internet absurdity.
    </p>
    <div class="about-pills" aria-label="Site traits">
      <span class="about-pill">Telegram-native</span>
      <span class="about-pill">Bilingual (EN/RU)</span>
      <span class="about-pill">Media-heavy</span>
      <span class="about-pill">Build-time tagging</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="about-columns" aria-label="What this archive contains">
    <article class="about-panel">
      <h2>What you will find</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Short one-message posts with image/video context.</li>
        <li>Longer multi-message threads when a topic needs depth.</li>
        <li>AI notes grounded in concrete examples, not abstract hype.</li>
        <li>Product and tooling takes from hands-on usage.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="about-panel">
      <h2>Editorial stance</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Minimal polishing: keep the original tone and timing.</li>
        <li>Date follows original Telegram message chronology.</li>
        <li>Strong opinions are allowed to age in public.</li>
        <li>Signal over perfection.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="about-link-grid" aria-label="Navigation shortcuts">
    <a class="about-link-card" href="/en/tags/">
      <h3>Browse by tag</h3>
      <p>Topic-first navigation from AI and coding to quick notes.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="about-link-card" href="/en/search/">
      <h3>Search threads</h3>
      <p>Full-text search over post bodies and metadata.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="about-link-card" href="/en/calendar/">
      <h3>View by timeline</h3>
      <p>Scan publishing bursts by year, month, and day.</p>
    </a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
